      name: 'How many recessed lights do I need in my kitchen?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'A general rule is one 6-inch recessed light per 4-5 square feet of kitchen space, placed about 3 feet from walls and 4-5 feet apart. A typical 150 sq ft Seattle kitchen needs 8-12 recessed lights. However, this depends on ceiling height, other light sources (pendants, under-cabinet), and personal preference. Always use dimmable LEDs so you can adjust brightness.' },
